         <abstract>
            <p>A computational method for determining the regulator of a real quadratic field $Q(\sqrt D)$ is described. This method makes use of the properties of the nearest integer continued fraction of $\sqrt D$ and is about $25%$ faster than methods which use the ordinary (integer part) continued fraction of $\sqrt D$. Several tables are also presented.</p>
